rComments: Her class was truly inspiring with deep consideration of students' level of understanding. As a first-year architecture course, the readings and assignments were all reasonable. Yet some memorization were needed.
Amzing, great and overall the best prof ever!!!
She's a great! As long as you go to the class and pay attention the tests become straight-forward.
Very helpful when approached in office hours.
OMG you're about to take a Zeynep class?!  - lucky duck.   - Seriously she's great. Pay attention, she's brilliant and has a lot to teach you.
not nice when you talk to her. not very helpful

Wonderful professor. Communicates expectations with perfect clarity, so her tests become pretty straight forward. She is creative in her presentation of difficult concepts and is able to present them in a straight forward way. However, without the lecture, her slide shows and presentations are vague and confusing. CLASS IS A MUST
She is a very clear speaker and her lectures are well understood. She brings up some interesting topics and is great to listen to
Professor Celik is amazing! She has a brilliant way of reducing complex architectural concepts into normal language.
No good. Stopped going to lectures when she included in a reading "ambivolence = time-space".

Great class, I also learned lots during her lecture. She keeps you interested during lecture, you won't fall sleep unless you don't like architecture. If you want to suceed in this course, you have to be present during lecture. I definitely recommend this course.

I disagree.  Learned a tremendous amount in her class.  She presented the material in a unique way. different from other art/arch history courses, presenting ideas driving the movements instead of dates to memorize, but also presenting opposing ideas that made you think/see it differently.  Well organized, intelligent, and great communicator.
Prof Celik seems nice and well meaning, but her tests and exams are arbitrary to say the least. Felt I learned very little in this class.
